14/05/2006
VIENNA, Austria -- Greek Prime Minister Costas Karamanlis and his Turkish counterpart, Recep Tayyip Erdogan, held a meeting in Vienna on Friday (12 May), within the framework of the EU- Latin America-Caribbean summit.
It was their second meeting in under two weeks.
According to media reports, discussions focused primarily on economic issues and tourism.
(Kathimerini - 13/05/06)
